definitions: Past tense and past participle of string.
To have put strings on an instrument or object.
To have arranged things in a line or series.
To have threaded beads or other items onto a string.
To have made tense or nervous.
examples: He strung the guitar last night.
The lights were strung across the patio.
She strung the pearls for the necklace.
The constant pressure strung him out.
